data.entity_name: Sensor Device and Method for the Detection of a Gripping of a Hand-Held Device as Well as a Hand-Held Device
data.content:
Sensor Device and Method for the Detection of a Gripping of a Hand-Held Device as Well as a Hand-Held Device
This is the title of the patent application describing a sensor device used to detect when a hand-held device is being gripped.

13808700
The Application Number refers to the unique identifier assigned to the patent application for tracking purposes.

PENDING
This denotes that the patent application is still under review and has not yet been officially granted or rejected.

H03K1796, G06F132, G01N2722
These are IPC labels assigned to classify the patent application according to specific technical fields.

Hand-Held Device
A hand-held device is an electronic gadget designed for portability and ease of use with one hand, such as smartphones or tablets.

Sensor Device
The Sensor Device is a technological component used to detect the gripping action on a hand-held device through capacitive coupling between electrodes.

First Electrode and Second Electrode
These are electrical components of the sensor device that work together to analyze capacitive coupling or load against reference ground.

Provider of Products and Services
The provider of products and services is an organization that sends encrypted NDEF messages to mobile devices for enabling secure transactions.

Mobile Device User
A person using a mobile device, configured to receive, decrypt, and use the NFC emulated card for making payments at the provider's place of business.

Point-of-Sale Terminal
The point-of-sale terminal is used by providers to authorize transactions initiated via an NFC-emulated card stored on a mobile device.

NFC Emulated Card
An NFC emulated card represents digital funds stored within the user's mobile device for facilitating payments at points of sale.

Over-the-Air Communications Standard
A wireless communication standard different from NFC, used by mobile devices to receive encrypted NDEF messages over the air.

Publication Number US20160335619A1-20161117
The publication number denotes the official release of technical details related to enabling secure transactions via mobile devices.

View Locking Multi-Monitor Screen Magnifier
A method of magnifying screen views across multiple monitors while maintaining view locking mechanisms to restrict pointer movement.
